column3: Prefer #10714 - GCC is technically correct here, its a race to hit fShutdown before the print, no reason to silence it, we should fix our bug.
This PR can be closed as [#10714](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/10714) has solved the problem this PR tried to address.

~~It doesn't look like #10714 solved the warning? after #10714 don't we just need to initialize nStart to 0 when it's declared or something?~~\n\nAlso, @ReneNyffenegger you can close your own PRs yourself if you want.
I didn't know I could close my pull requests. Doing it now.
